text: (1)  Ultrasonic Examination (UE) System Standardization.
label: BODY

text: Prior to retesting each specific cylinder design and
label: BODY

text: type, the UE system must be standardized for testing by
label: BODY

text: using a standard reference. The standard reference must
label: BODY

text: be similar (material of construction, size, wall
label: BODY

text: thickness, etc.) to the identified cylinders to be
label: BODY

text: tested. Standardization of the UE system must be
label: BODY

text: performed by using a relevant reference cylinder that is
label: BODY

text: described in paragraph 7.c. of this special permit. The
label: BODY

text: standardization of the UE system is as follows:
label: BODY

text: (i)  A reference cylinder with an artificial defect
label: BODY

text: made to represent area corrosion must be placed in
label: BODY

text: the UE system. The UE system must be standardized to
label: BODY

text: indicate rejection for an area equal or greater than
label: BODY

text: the machined surface for the cylinder (0.70 in2).
label: BODY

text: Where the wall thickness is reduced below tm, a
label: BODY

text: straight ultrasound beam must be used to measure the
label: BODY

text: wall thickness of the machined area.
label: BODY

text: (ii)  A reference cylinder with a FBH made to
label: BODY

text: represent an isolated pit must be placed in the UE
label: BODY

text: system. The FBH must be detected by a minimum of two
label: BODY

text: shear wave beams that strike the FBH from opposite
label: BODY

text: sides (e.g. the first shear wave direction is from
label: BODY

text: top to bottom of the cylinder and the second
label: BODY

text: shear wave direction is from the bottom to top).
label: BODY

text: The UE gain must be increased until the signal from
label: BODY

text: FBH is maximized at 80 percent of the screen height.
label: BODY

text: (iii)  A reference cylinder with circumferential
label: BODY

text: notches made to represent line corrosion must be
label: BODY

text: placed in the UE system. Each internal and external
label: BODY

text: notch must be detected by a minimum of one shear
label: BODY

text: wave beam. The UE gain must be increased until the
label: BODY

text: signal from each notch is maximized at 80 percent of
label: BODY

text: the screen height.
label: BODY

text: (iv)  A reference cylinder with longitudinal notches
label: BODY

text: to represent a longitudinal sidewall crack (LSC)
label: BODY

text: must be placed in the UE system. Each internal and
label: BODY

text: external notch must be detected by a minimum of two
label: BODY

text: shear wave beams that strike the LSC from opposite
label: BODY

text: directions (e.g. the first shear wave direction is
label: BODY

text: clockwise and second shear wave direction is
label: BODY
